<TITLE> Pabna transport strike enters second day </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, Sep 1 (bdnews24.com)A transport strike in Pabna continued for a second day on Tuesday, severing the northwest district's ties with the rest of the country. The strike was enforced on Monday to protest damage to vehicles following the death of a college student in a road accident on Sunday. Selim Hasan, 22, a student of the management of Pabna Edward University College, was fatallly injured after he was crushed under the wheels of a bus. He succumbed to his injuries on Sunday night at Rajshahi Medical College Hospital. The students of the college organised a protest rally in the town on Monday morning and vandalised vehicles on the road. Pabna District Tranport Owners and Workers Unity Association called an indefinite period in protest. Movement of inter-district buses and trucks and Pabna-Dhaka road communications remained suspended due to the strike, caused sufferings to people. Convener of the Unity Association Baby Islam said bdnews24.com, "The administration did not take any initiative to arrest the guilty. The strike will continue if they do not meet our demand." bdnews24
